body:
Using AutoMapper version 3.1.0.1032 with EntityFramework 5.  Attempting to use the projection features of AutoMapper.

Consider the following:

```
namespace Domain
{    
   public class Scenario
   {
       public int Id { get; set; }
       public string Name { get; set; }
       public ICollection<Domain.Characteristic> Characteristics { get; set; }
   }

    public class Characteristic
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
    }
}


namespace Models
{
    public class Scenario
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
        public ICollection<Models.Characteristic> Characteristics { get; set; }
    }

    public class Characteristic
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
    }
}
```

And the following AutoMapperConfiguration

```
Mapper.CreateMap<Domain.Scenario, Models.Scenario>();
Mapper.CreateMap<Domain.Characteristic, Models.Characteristic>();
```

When this is executed:

```
IQueryable<Models.Scenario> query = 
    context
      .Set<Domain.Scenario>()
      .Include("Characteristics")
      .Project()
      .To<Models.Scenario>();
```

AutoMapper has an exception in this method:

```
private static Expression CreateMapExpression(IMappingEngine mappingEngine, Type typeIn, Type typeOut, Expression instanceParameter)

```

In this else block:

```
else
{
  // destination type implements ienumerable, but is not an ilist. allow deferred enumeration
  bindExpression = Expression.Bind(destinationMember, selectExpression);
}
```

With an ArgumentException "Argument types do not match"

If instead, the objects looked as such:

```
namespace Domain
{    
   public class Scenario
   {
       public int Id { get; set; }
       public string Name { get; set; }
       public ICollection<Domain.Characteristic> Characteristics { get; set; }
   }

    public class Characteristic
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
    }
}


namespace Models
{
    public class Scenario
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
        public ICollection<Domain.Characteristic> Characteristics { get; set; }
    }
}
```

Everything is projected fine.
